FBIS4-16480 "drsov074_d_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 Regional Affairs New Moscow Criminal Police Head on Crime Code New Moscow Criminal Police Head on Crime Code MK1504120094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 15 Apr 94 p 1 MK1504120094 Moscow SEGODNYA Russian BFN [Lyudmila Pivovarova report: "New Moscow Criminal Investigation Administration Chief Urges Criminal Code Be Tightened"] [Text] Vasiliy Kuptsov has been appointed the new chief of the Moscow Criminal Investigations Administration. Mr. Kuptsov has said in his first brief interview that the country's Criminal Code is outdated and still rooted in socialism, whereas society has long been trying to adopt a capitalist way of life. The new Moscow Criminal Investigation Administration chief is certain that many provisions of the Criminal Code should be tightened and that crime should be combated not by one single agency, but by "the entire community," while his subordinates "are ready to combat crime and to defend the law."
